programme.title: Paul O'Grady: For the Love of Dogs
programme.desc: Paul O'Grady returns to Battersea Dogs and Cats Home to meet more of the canine residents who are looking for love, help, understanding and a new home. In this opening episode, Paul meets aged mongrel Hope, whose dramatic arrival is causing concern for the staff. She has only ever had one owner who is now too old to look after her. Hope is petrified of her new surroundings and shuts down, refusing to go for a walk or even eat. Can Paul help lighten her mood? If not, who will ever want to give this old lady a new home? Paul then has his hands full trying to help an abandoned doberman-cross pup found cowering under a car. Finally, there is Titch, probably the scruffiest dog ever to enter the gates at Battersea. His coat is so dirty and matted that he can hardly walk. So it is off to the barbers for Titch - but what will he make of his new extreme hair do? Can Paul find anyone willing to rehome a totally bald dog?(n)

programme.title: Paul O'Grady: For the Love of Dogs
programme.desc: Paul O'Grady returns to Battersea Dogs and Cats Home to meet more of the canine residents who are looking for love, help, understanding and a new home. In this opening episode, Paul meets aged mongrel Hope, whose dramatic arrival is causing concern for the staff. She has only ever had one owner who is now too old to look after her. Hope is petrified of her new surroundings and shuts down, refusing to go for a walk or even eat. Can Paul help lighten her mood? If not, who will ever want to give this old lady a new home? Paul then has his hands full trying to help an abandoned doberman-cross pup found cowering under a car. Finally, there is Titch, probably the scruffiest dog ever to enter the gates at Battersea. His coat is so dirty and matted that he can hardly walk. So it is off to the barbers for Titch - but what will he make of his new extreme hair do? Can Paul find anyone willing to rehome a totally bald dog?(n)
